2ï¸âƒ£ What exactly is systemd?
Simple definition:

systemd is the first program started by the kernel, and it manages the entire system.

It starts services

It stops services

It monitors services

It restarts failed services

It handles boot order

ğŸ“Œ systemd = system manager

