ğŸš€ No guessing, no race conditions

ğŸ”Ÿ systemctl â€“ how we control systemd

systemctl = command to talk to systemd

Common commands:
systemctl status nginx
systemctl start nginx
systemctl stop nginx
systemctl restart nginx
systemctl enable nginx
systemctl disable nginx

Meaning:

start â†’ start now

enable â†’ start on boot

status â†’ health check

1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ How systemd handles failures

If a service crashes:

systemd detects it

Restarts it automatically (if configured)

Logs the failure

Logs:

journalctl -u nginx


ğŸ‘‰ This is very important for production & DevOps.

1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ systemd vs old init (why systemd is better)
Old init	                     systemd
Starts services one by one	   Parallel startup
No dependency handling	      Dependency aware
Weak logging	               Powerful logging
Slow boot	                  Fast boot

